  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of the study is to implement and measure the efficiency of a standardized acute
      and brief non-pharmacological intervention (Cognitive interventions on Sleep - Anxiety -
      Attention - Memory) following mild TBI and observe their impact pre- and post-treatments. The
      ultimate goal is to have patients be re-integrated to their activities faster with lesser
      symptoms and have patients present lesser post-concussive symptoms. Specific objectives: 1)
      Measure the effect of an acute and brief non-pharmacological intervention on PCS symptoms,
      sleep, headaches, affect, cognition and functional outcome following mild TBI; 2)To redefine
      a model of outcome prediction following mild TBI.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
